Package: creativity
Section: science
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Pre-Depends: ${misc:Pre-Depends}
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Economic creativity and piracy simulator (command-line tools)
 Creativity is an economics agent-based model that simulates the creative process,
 including creation, sales, and piracy of creative works.
 .
 This package contains the command-line tools for running creativity
 simulations and analyzing the results:
 .
 creativity-cli -- runs a simulation
 creativity-random -- draws simulation settings from random distributions
 creativity-info -- displays summary information for a saved simulation
 creativity-data -- builds a data file from one or more simulations
 creativity-results -- analyzes data generated by creativity-data

Package: creativity-gui
Section: science
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Pre-Depends: ${misc:Pre-Depends}
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Suggests: creativity
Description: Economic creativity and piracy simulator (GTK3 interface)
 Creativity is an economics agent-based model that simulates the creative process,
 including creation, sales, and piracy of creative works.
 .
 This package contains the GTK3 graphical interface to running and viewing new
 and saved creativity simulations.

